JOHANNESBURG - Tributes have poured in for late jazz great, Ray Phiri from all over the world. But none have been more touching than those from his South African fans.When eNCA asked locals for their messages on the music icon, we were inundated.Phiri (70) passed way in a Mbombela hospital in the early hours of Wednesday morning following a battle with lung cancer.Even President Jacob Zuma called Phiri was a musical giant in a statement."This is indeed a huge loss for South Africa and the music industry as a whole. We are with his family in thoughts and prayers during this trying period. May his soul rest in peace, Zuma said.Phiri was the founder of Stimela, with whom he conceived gold and platinum-selling albums like Fire, Passion and Ecstacy, and Look, Listen and Decide.His music career spanned four decades.